<item>
            <title>[HBASE-13367] Add a replication label to mutations from replication</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-13367</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In some scenarios, the regions need to distinguish the mutations from client for actual users or from replication of peer cluster. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Lower the priority of mutations from replication to improve the latency of requests from actuals users&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Set table in replicated state to keep data consistent. In this state, the table will reject mutations from users, but accept mutations from replication and read requests from users.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;So we need to add a replication label to mutations from replication.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Suggestions and discussions are welcomed. Thanks&lt;/p&gt;</description>
